<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>14674</anchor> <rss>jms-0083.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-0083</addr>  <route>jms-0083.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="jms-0082.xml" type="local" title="The Karoubi envelope">Karoubi envelopes</link> are unique</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>C</tex> be a category; then the type of <link href="jms-0082.xml" type="local" title="The Karoubi envelope">Karoubi envelopes</link> <tex>C \to   \widetilde{C}</tex> for <tex>C</tex> is contractible.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>14675</anchor> <rss>jms-0082.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0082</addr>  <route>jms-0082.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The Karoubi envelope</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A functor <tex>C \to \widetilde{C}</tex> is said to exhibit <tex>\widetilde{C}</tex> as an <em>Karoubi envelope</em> or <em>idempotent completion</em> of <tex>C</tex> when <tex>C \to \widetilde{C}</tex> is fully faithful, <tex>\widetilde{C}</tex> is idempotent complete, and every object of <tex>\widetilde{C}</tex> is a retract of (the image of) an object of <tex>C</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>